  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "xpath=(.//*[normalize-space(text()) and normalize-space(.)='Roth IRA'])[1]/following::p[1]",
      "value": "When you convert to a Roth IRA, you owe income taxes for that year on the amount you are converting. However, if you made the conversion in 2010, you could pay one-half of the taxes due on the conversion in 2011 and the other half in 2012. You do not owe income taxes on any nondeductible amounts that you convert. The amount of annual contributions that you are allowed to make to a deductible or Roth IRA phases out at higher incomes."
